README for Lab1 solution of CMPS12B.

C. Seshadhri, Sept 2017
=====================================

Solution files: HelloUser.java, HelloUser2.java, Makefile1, Makefile2, Makefile3, README

=====================================

The aim of this Lab is to learn to use makefiles. The jar files created here are basically
Hello World programs, with some extra system information printed.


Instruction to run solution
--------------------------------------
Let $ denote the prompt. 

$ make -f Makefile1

Creates jar HelloUser.jar.

$ java -jar HelloUser.jar

Prints "Hello <username>" followed by system details.

$ make -f Makefile1 clean

Deletes HelloUser class and jar files.
All the above holds for Makefile2.

$ make -f Makefile3

Creates Hello.jar.

$ java -jar Hello.jar

Prints "Hello <username>"

$ make -f Makefile3 clean

Deletes HelloUser1, HelloUser2 class files and Hello.jar

